items.name: TruckMaker
items.description:
TruckMaker is a tool for generating all types of trucks. It was trained on an in-house generated dataset of 120 designs with interesting concept features. The model either fixes the input or makes it more interesting for variations.

SDXL (1024x1024) note: use also negative weights, check examples

SD 1.5: LyCORIS/LoHA experiment trained 768x768, NR 32 + NA 16 dimensions.

Use Hires. fix (4x_RealisticRescaler, 4x-Ultrasharp upscale with denoising strength around 0.3-0.6) for best details in txt2img!

You can combine it with my other car models for added (sur)realism. Check the gallery for examples.

Experiment with weights around 0.4-1, CLIP SKIP 1-2 (2 works better for some stylized models). The model works with a truck token (try to use a combination like firetruck, monstertruck, fueltruck). It will also style a combined vehicle.

For my notes on training and use of stable diffusion models, check https://sandner.art/articles/ai/

If you can afford it, support my work by buying me a coffee to keep those render cores go: https://ko-fi.com/airesearch

Have fun rendering!

items.name: Hyperdimension Neptunia - IF / 超次元ゲイム ネプテューヌ - アイエフ
items.description:
Weight 1 works well. Prompting; if, green eyes, hair bow, works great for her general appearance, i.e. the hair structure and bow? placement. Add in brown hair, long hair, if needed. However, it seems to not, as the preview data shows I didn't need it. Mileage may vary.

For her basic outfit; black tank top, bike shorts

For her full outfit; blue jacket, fur trim, open jacket, oversized clothes, black tank top, bike shorts, socks, kneehighs, boots, cross-laced footwear

Adjust for the shot. No need for legwear in a portrait/profile/upper body prompt.

This LoRA has a Net Dim of 18 with an Alpha Rank of 9, slightly heavier like my Minazuki LoRA. Larger size allows for picking out details, but also a drawback as it lets in more unwanted data. So you'll have to do some general prompting for a non-solid color background, and to get her to stand in a full body prompt.

Trained on 27 images, most of them received varying levels of editing.

Still not sure if her leaf thing is a bow, ribbon, or a (leaf) hair ornament, but the LoRA responded much better to hair bow. So that's what ended up in the dataset.

items.name: Matsuda Yuusuke Style
items.description:
A style with fairly strong line-work and colors with a chibi touch.

How to use
Just prompt away as normal. Things to try is putting "3D" and/or "realistic" in negatives if your model has a lot of that mixed in. You can also try adding "chibi" as positive tag at various strength. Dataset contains mainly various monster/demon/etc girls, predominately with horns, so the LoRA is especially good at that but it works well with standard issue girls as well.

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

MISC
Trained on NAI at 768 resolution with a dataset of 98 images.
All images are raw txt2img upscaled without any helper embeddings.

items.name: Katheryn Winnick (JG version)
items.description:
A commission of @Zorglub.

Note: I suggest you also check @sstylerdurden879 fantastic version, linked here.

Katheryn Winnick is a Canadian actress mainly known for her role as Lagertha in the TV show Vikings.

1500-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (k4tw1nn1ck:0.99), a woman as a movie star, freckles, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

Edward Scissorhands is not in the dataset, on purpose, to avoid making hands bad.

I had a lot of fun using it. Should work around weight 1 on AR.


How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

Teeth can be a little bit tricky, it's quite easy to get muddy or distorted face if your canvas size is small; however, the problem can be resolved rather easily with upscale, hire fix or inpaint.

Attack titan is quite good at punching due to inclusion in the data, so you can include punching in the prompt if you want a more dynamic pose; it is possible to generate armor on fist which you can also include in the prompt, but this is rather unstable for now, I will probably work on that in future.

items.name: donkira_slider
items.description:
donkira_sliderは、画風を変更させるためのLoRAです。

通常の適用で黒目を小さく、彩度は低く、低精細にし、マイナス適用で黒目を大きく、彩度は高く、高精細なイラストに変化させます。

想定強度は、-0.8～1.0。

-1でも問題はありませんが、多少手指の崩壊が見られたので、作者保証はこの数値までとします。

"どんより"と"キラキラ"、一挙両得のLoRAとしてお使いください。

Donkira_slider is a LoRA designed to alter the style of illustrations.

In its normal application, it reduces the size of the pupils, lowers the saturation, and decreases the level of detail in the illustration.

In negative application, it enlarges the pupils, increases the saturation, and enhances the detail in the illustration.

The expected intensity ranges from -0.8 to 1.0.

Although there's no issue with going as low as -1, there may be slight distortions in the fingers, so the creator's warranty covers up to this range.

Please use it as a versatile LoRA to achieve both 'gloomy' and 'sparkling' effects.

Put the comic you want in the prompt after the lora. I haven't tested multiple comics, but Batman, Superman and Archie worked well. I used the Babes model for this LoRA and it works great. If you lower the weight of the LoRA <lora:SChevrier-04:0.7> you can get her kind of style of woman without the comic book face. Enjoy!

items.name: Síofra Cipher
items.description:
Síofra Cipher is a person who doesn't exist. You can use her if you need a consistent character.

Please have a look at other Nobody models for contributions by other folks including those created with the LastName and NBDY tags.

Follow me if you'd like to be notified of future models!

Freckles and Red Hair

If you've ever tried to get freckles using Stable Diffusion you know they can be a challenge. A lot of times they simply look like a uniform pattern of dots or they don't work at all. You might see that with this model as well -- if you do I would suggest trying a different base model OR adding freckles to your negative prompt.

Red hair can also be tough sometimes for SD -- you might notice Síofra's hair generate very bright red. To mitigate this I would add a little bit more noise with something like LowRA ( see Suggested Resources below).

Installation

To install, download the .bin file and then place in the stable-diffusion-webui/embeddings/ folder. Then you'll either need to restart WebUI or tap the Refresh button in the Textual Inversions tab in the Extra Networks tab.

To Use

The trigger word is SiofraCipher which you can use in your prompt. See the gallery below for some examples. For InvokeAI it should be <siofracipher>

A note about what I use to generate images

  • My main go-to photorealistic models right now are RealisticVision 2.0 and ICBINP.

  • I always use the vae-ft-mse-840000 as my VAE. You can find it at HuggingFace. You can enable the VAE dropdown menu in WebUI by going to Settings -> User Interface -> Quicksettings list and adding "sd_vae"

  • To upscale I'll use a combination of ControlNet 1.1's tile_resample/tile model and Ultimate SD Upscaler
